Defendant Damon Fitzgerald Murphy in court with attorney Jeffrey J Guerard.  Defendant Damon Fitzgerald Murphy in custody.  Ronald Dague appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy court clerk:  vk  

Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant. 
As to Count 1:  The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of  5 YEARS CONCURRENT with Count 2 ; the INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 2 YEARS; the MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION is 3 YEARS.
As to Count 2:  The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of  5 YEARS CONCURRENT with Count 1 ; the INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 2 YEARS; the MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION is 3 YEARS.
No days credit.
These sentences are consecutive with any other sentence.
Court stayed the sentences and place the defendant  on 3 years probation.
Court finds defendant IS NOT eligible for the Challenge Incarceration program or the WI Substance Abuse program.   
Conditions of Probation/ Extended Supervision if revoked:
- No further violations rising to the level of probable cause
- Cooperate with the Probation Department
- 50 hours of community service
- No possession of alcohol or illegal drugs
- Random urine screens
- Seek and maintain full-time employment
- Provide a DNA sample.
Court orders no other specific programming conditions.  Defendant must complete a risk and needs assessment with DOC and comply with case plan goals related to prioritized need areas so identified. 

Court ordered the defendant pay all of the following by the end of supervision.  Failure to pay will result in a civil judgment:
Restitution in the amount of $382.40 to Frank J
Pay DNA surcharges;
Pay court costs
All applicable fees of supervision.
-  No Cash Bail Posted in this matter
-  If revoked, the Court ordered that all court costs, fines, surcharges and/or restitution be paid through collection by the Department of Corrections from 25% of funds under Sec. 973.05(4)(b) and as a condition of extended supervision. DOC shall collect those sums.  Any amount remaining due and owing is subject to civil judgment and/or tax intercept or other means.

Court advised defendant that as a convicted felon he may never possess a firearm. 
Court advised defendant of his right to seek postconviction relief.
Court advised defendant that he may not vote until his civil rights have been restored.

Defendant Damon Fitzgerald Murphy in court with attorney Jeffrey J Guerard.  Defendant Damon Fitzgerald Murphy in custody.  Ronald Dague appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy court clerk:  vk  Defendant was advised of constitutional rights and maximum penalties, waived all rights, plead GUILTY and was examined as to the plea.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights and Addendum received and filed.  Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis for the plea.  Defendant further advised that if he is not a US citizen deportation is possible.  Court found defendant guilty as charged in the Information and ordered entry of Judgment of Conviction.  
Court advised defendant that as a convicted felon he may never possess a firearm.  Court advised defendant that his voting rights are suspended, and may not vote in any election until his civil rights are restored. Court orders defendant provide a DNA sample.  Court REMANDS the defendant.
Case is adjourned for sentencing in Branch 19.  Sentencing hearing scheduled for December 2, 2015 at 01:30 pm.
